SEARCH
Package com.smsapp.util

Class Queries

java.lang.Object
com.smsapp.util.Queries
public class Queries extends Object
Contains SQL query strings used in the School Management System application.

This class provides a collection of String constants that represent SQL queries for various operations in the school management system. These queries cover CRUD operations for entities such as students, teachers, exams, and addresses, as well as queries for managing relationships between these entities.

The queries include operations for:

  • Inserting, updating, and deleting records in the student, teacher, address, and exam tables.
  • Retrieving records from the student, teacher, address, and exam tables by ID and other criteria.
  • Managing many-to-many relationships between student, teacher, and exam entities.
  • Calculating total marks for students based on exam records.

The SQL queries are designed to be used with PreparedStatement objects, where parameters are represented by placeholders (question marks ?). They are organized as public static final String fields for easy access throughout the application.

The fields in this class include:

  • INSERT_ADDRESS
  • INSERT_STUDENT
  • GET_STUDENT_BY_ID
